The paper discusses the development of a framework for robust training of Graph Neural Networks (GNNs), which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also addresses the issue of adversarial attacks on GNNs, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the application of the proposed framework to computer vision (cs.CV) and social network analysis (cs.SI), which are subfields of computer science that are closely related to GNNs.
